00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:51.400
You've been here five months.

00:00:52.019 --> 00:00:53.079
You've come a long way.

00:00:53.719 --> 00:00:55.420
Your body has done a lot of healing.

00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.200
Except for my hands.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.039
They're never gonna get better, and that means I'll never draw again.

00:01:03.119 --> 00:01:04.680
And that's the only thing that I was ever good at.

00:01:06.239 --> 00:01:08.060
You suffered severe nerve damage.

00:01:08.159 --> 00:01:10.760
It's lucky that you have any movement in your hands at all.

00:01:11.439 --> 00:01:13.239
I did everything I could, you know that.

00:01:13.260 --> 00:01:13.500
Really?

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:17.260
Is that what you told the five patients who filed malpractice suits against you?

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:21.799
Now, I can understand you're still being angry.

00:01:22.500 --> 00:01:24.939
But blaming me isn't gonna change your condition.

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:28.140
You were in an accident, and you have to accept that.

00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:29.680
I was in a hit-and-run.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:36.060
You know, when I was your age, I wanted to be a violinist.

00:01:36.319 --> 00:01:40.060
So I applied to the conservatory, but I failed the audition.

00:01:40.879 --> 00:01:43.780
Instructor told me that I had the hands of a surgeon.

00:01:44.799 --> 00:01:46.760
And that's why I moved into medicine.

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:51.299
As one door closes, another one opens.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.599
You're young. You'll find something new.

00:01:58.200 --> 00:01:59.099
Goodbye, Justin.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:00.859
Goodbye, Justin.

00:02:05.239 --> 00:02:06.780
