00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:06.720
I see you in a uniform flying.

00:05:07.980 --> 00:05:09.720
You ever considered a career in the Air Force?

00:05:10.839 --> 00:05:11.860
Um, I'll think about it.

00:05:16.500 --> 00:05:17.639
What are you smiling about?

00:05:18.620 --> 00:05:20.740
I just landed a summer job at Mayor Siegel's office

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:22.240
working on his re-election campaign.

00:05:22.480 --> 00:05:24.399
I thought you were gonna help your mom out down at the courthouse.

00:05:24.399 --> 00:05:28.159
Judge Roski gets some KSU students to schlep her files.

00:05:28.599 --> 00:05:30.620
Besides, who wants to hang out with their parents all summer long?

00:05:30.979 --> 00:05:32.339
Yeah. Sorry, Clark.

00:05:33.299 --> 00:05:35.459
Did you know there's Kwan's son down at the Air Force booth?

00:05:36.620 --> 00:05:39.000
Growing up with Kwan, the Air Force most seemed like club men.

00:05:40.759 --> 00:05:41.779
Wow, you look nice.

00:05:42.060 --> 00:05:44.139
Thanks. I was kind of going for professional.

00:05:44.339 --> 00:05:46.859
Did you know that the Daily Planet only takes four high school interns

00:05:46.859 --> 00:05:47.719
from the whole state?

00:05:48.139 --> 00:05:49.199
Oh, yeah, sure, and Chloe?

00:05:49.759 --> 00:05:50.459
Tell him that.

00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:53.060
He said they received over 500 applicants last year.

00:05:53.560 --> 00:05:54.379
I doubt I'll even get a chance to do that.

00:05:54.399 --> 00:05:54.839
I thought you had an interview.

00:05:55.519 --> 00:05:56.539
Well, there's always the Inquisitor.

00:05:56.759 --> 00:05:57.779
Didn't Lex offer to hook you up?

00:05:57.899 --> 00:05:59.279
No. I'm interning at the Planet.

00:05:59.399 --> 00:06:02.060
I don't care if it's delivering coffee to the classified department.

00:06:02.299 --> 00:06:04.939
Why don't you just try again next Saturday when you're in Metropolis?

00:06:05.439 --> 00:06:06.279
Why are you going to Metropolis?

00:06:09.939 --> 00:06:11.459
We're going to Metropolis, Clark.

00:06:12.459 --> 00:06:13.639
The student journalism conference?

00:06:15.299 --> 00:06:17.099
You were supposed to sign us up,

00:06:17.159 --> 00:06:19.539
and I know you didn't forget because now it's too late to get in.

00:06:19.679 --> 00:06:20.620
I'm really sorry.

00:06:20.959 --> 00:06:23.519
I've been at the Talon all week with Lana working on a history project.

00:06:24.399 --> 00:06:26.139
So, naturally, everything else becomes less important.

00:06:26.359 --> 00:06:27.219
Whoa, that's not true.

00:06:29.339 --> 00:06:31.679
Clark, how much time have we spent together in the last three weeks?

00:06:31.779 --> 00:06:32.799
We see each other every day.

00:06:33.019 --> 00:06:36.399
It was 45 minutes when my car happened to break down outside the Talon

00:06:36.399 --> 00:06:37.479
and you gave me a ride home.

00:06:37.739 --> 00:06:39.899
I practically had to tear you away from Lana.

00:06:40.120 --> 00:06:41.639
Don't you think you're being just a little unfair?

00:06:41.679 --> 00:06:44.479
No. Whenever Lex and Lana are around, it's like the rest of us don't exist.

00:06:44.959 --> 00:06:46.959
Wait, Chloe, why are you being so hypersensitive?

00:06:48.399 --> 00:06:50.079
You know, most men are from Mars, Clark,

00:06:50.079 --> 00:06:52.779
but you're from some distant galaxy that I've never even heard of.

00:06:54.399 --> 00:06:57.799
Look, I know I screwed up, but why is Chloe having a breakdown?

00:06:58.099 --> 00:07:00.120
You're not the most observant person in the world, are you?

00:07:00.339 --> 00:07:01.339
What are you talking about?

00:07:01.819 --> 00:07:03.599
She wanted to spend a day with you uninterrupted.

00:07:03.639 --> 00:07:04.739
No Lana and no Lex.

00:07:05.159 --> 00:07:06.979
She was planning on asking you to the spring formal.

00:07:07.099 --> 00:07:08.339
Yeah, but that'd be like...

00:07:09.060 --> 00:07:09.439
Date?

00:07:11.599 --> 00:07:13.719
Clark, maybe if you took off your Lana blinders,

00:07:13.959 --> 00:07:15.399
you'd realize that Chloe likes you.

00:07:23.339 --> 00:07:23.779
Clark?

00:07:23.779 --> 00:07:23.859
Clark?

00:07:24.399 --> 00:07:26.399
I'm interested in an apology.

00:07:26.439 --> 00:07:28.439
Well, not the welcome I was expecting, but hi.

00:07:28.479 --> 00:07:31.479
Hey! How are you? It's so good to see you.

00:07:31.519 --> 00:07:32.519
When did you get back?

00:07:32.560 --> 00:07:33.560
Yesterday.

00:07:33.599 --> 00:07:35.439
Listen, I just wanted to thank you, by the way,

00:07:35.479 --> 00:07:37.159
for sending all those emails.

00:07:37.199 --> 00:07:39.199
They really got me through a tough time.

00:07:39.239 --> 00:07:41.839
Well, I'm sure that lots of people kept in touch.

00:07:41.879 --> 00:07:42.879
Yeah, you'd be surprised.

00:07:42.919 --> 00:07:44.919
For most of my friends, it was out of sight, out of mind.

00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:46.399
I know the feeling.

00:07:46.919 --> 00:07:48.919
So when can you start drawing your cartoon again?

00:07:48.959 --> 00:07:50.679
Everybody's been waiting for the further adventures

00:07:50.719 --> 00:07:52.719
of the Flaming Crow's Feet.

00:07:54.399 --> 00:07:57.639
Because that's the goal with just creating.

00:07:58.919 --> 00:08:01.000
Sure, but I'll visit V木き.

00:08:01.039 --> 00:08:03.039
встреч.

00:08:03.799 --> 00:08:05.819
Who could talk to you about Karna?

00:08:05.839 --> 00:08:06.579
Yourzejsa.

00:08:06.620 --> 00:08:08.439
Everybody else had good time,

00:08:08.479 --> 00:08:10.079
and are still sitting here talking.

00:08:10.120 --> 00:08:11.500
Is that make sense to you?

00:08:11.519 --> 00:08:12.199
Yeah...

00:08:13.859 --> 00:08:15.560
Once you could...

00:08:16.339 --> 00:08:17.419
Tak.

00:08:18.299 --> 00:08:19.519
I'm sorry.

00:08:19.560 --> 00:08:21.079
I'm sorry too.

00:08:21.159 --> 00:08:22.219
Okay.

00:08:22.220 --> 00:08:24.320
Yeah, why not?

00:08:24.320 --> 00:08:26.560
I'm in the process of reevaluating my life, too.

00:08:52.220 --> 00:08:59.920
What are you doing here?

00:09:02.940 --> 00:09:05.600
I'm here for the same reason you are.

00:09:07.379 --> 00:09:09.000
The anniversary of her death.

00:09:10.019 --> 00:09:11.240
It's been nine years.

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.720
Why the sudden burst of sentimentality?

00:09:15.160 --> 00:09:17.960
I deserve that. Just disappearing from your life, I...

00:09:17.960 --> 00:09:21.080
