00:14:26.320 --> 00:14:27.100
Careful, Clark.

00:14:27.180 --> 00:14:28.259
You almost sound a little jealous.

00:14:28.680 --> 00:14:29.500
I'm not jealous.

00:14:29.640 --> 00:14:30.560
I'm concerned.

00:14:30.900 --> 00:14:31.280
Why?

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:32.840
Because Chloe's falling for a nice guy?

00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.040
That's got me worried, too.

00:14:34.360 --> 00:14:34.640
Look.

00:14:36.440 --> 00:14:38.140
Justin had that in his portfolio yesterday.

00:14:40.560 --> 00:14:41.280
Going down.

00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:43.860
Doctor loses hands in freak accident.

00:14:44.640 --> 00:14:44.900
So?

00:14:44.900 --> 00:14:46.180
That was Justin's.

00:14:46.240 --> 00:14:46.500
Doctor?

00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:50.100
Don't you think it's a little weird he's carrying that around with him?

00:14:50.620 --> 00:14:52.000
I liked the tragic irony.

00:14:54.340 --> 00:14:56.259
You always talk about people behind their backs, Clark?

00:14:56.460 --> 00:14:57.480
Look, Justin, I didn't mean...

00:14:57.480 --> 00:14:57.980
Yes, you did.

00:14:58.640 --> 00:14:59.180
So what?

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:00.640
So I started spending a little time with Chloe,

00:15:00.759 --> 00:15:02.520
suddenly realized she exists and wore me out of the picture?

00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:04.580
Chloe and I are just friends.

00:15:05.259 --> 00:15:06.340
You had your chance with her.

00:15:07.980 --> 00:15:09.100
And you let me have mine.

00:15:16.540 --> 00:15:17.440
Did you cheat Chineseiros?

00:15:17.500 --> 00:15:18.259
Eric, are you nuts?

00:15:18.259 --> 00:15:18.620
Yes.

00:15:18.680 --> 00:15:19.100
Who?

00:15:19.140 --> 00:15:20.440
Just out of train.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:22.440
I still didn't get into it.

00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:22.759
Why?

00:15:22.759 --> 00:15:24.680
I thought you wouldn't.

00:15:24.680 --> 00:15:26.000
Was she your wife?

00:15:26.040 --> 00:15:26.340
Yes.

00:15:26.340 --> 00:15:28.660
Oh, yeah, I was just as sorry.

00:15:28.660 --> 00:15:29.240
I shopped for her.

00:15:29.300 --> 00:15:29.780
So this is it.

00:15:30.720 --> 00:15:31.820
Well, understand...

00:15:31.860 --> 00:15:37.379
Sameандria is

00:15:37.840 --> 00:15:42.280
The first man that came down here?

00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:43.900
But I...

00:15:43.900 --> 00:15:44.759
Here it says...

00:15:44.759 --> 00:15:45.040
Who?

00:15:45.040 --> 00:15:45.460
Wait.

00:15:45.460 --> 00:15:47.800
You were an employee, Mrs. Jenkins.

00:15:47.800 --> 00:15:50.000
You were paid to watch me while my mother's health failed

00:15:50.000 --> 00:15:53.600
and my father crisscrossed the globe on business.

00:15:53.600 --> 00:15:55.800
I loved you like my own.

00:15:55.800 --> 00:15:58.139
After the meteor shower, I was the one person

00:15:58.139 --> 00:15:59.940
who never looked at you differently.

00:16:02.440 --> 00:16:05.139
Just because you knew me at a vulnerable point in my life

00:16:05.139 --> 00:16:08.860
doesn't give you the right to waltz back in here a decade later.

00:16:08.860 --> 00:16:12.860
Things have changed. I've changed.

00:16:12.860 --> 00:16:14.480
What do you want from me?

00:16:14.480 --> 00:16:16.820
I want you to know what really happened.

00:16:16.820 --> 00:16:20.820
You lied to my mother on her deathbed.

00:16:20.820 --> 00:16:22.320
No, I didn't.

00:16:22.320 --> 00:16:25.820
I had every intention of staying, but your father sent me away.

00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:28.820
After the funeral, he called me into his office

00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:31.820
and he told me if I ever had contact with you again

00:16:31.820 --> 00:16:33.740
that he would disinherit you.

00:16:33.740 --> 00:16:35.539
Why would he do that?

00:16:35.539 --> 00:16:38.539
Because he wanted you to be his son, not hers.

00:16:38.539 --> 00:16:41.539
So why show up now?

00:16:41.539 --> 00:16:43.039
Hmm?

00:16:43.039 --> 00:16:44.420
Does the statute of limitations

00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:44.480
allow you to do that?

00:16:44.480 --> 00:16:48.480
Has my father's threat expired?

00:16:48.480 --> 00:16:50.820
I needed to see if you'd found a way to be true to yourself

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:53.480
in spite of Lionel's efforts.

00:16:56.460 --> 00:16:58.980
And to be honest, I...

00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:00.800
I wanted your forgiveness.

00:17:04.799 --> 00:17:07.799
I'm afraid you'll have to find a way to grant it to yourself.

00:17:13.640 --> 00:17:14.420
Goodbye, Alex.

00:17:14.420 --> 00:17:30.800
I wish everything sold as well as your mom's organic apple pies.

00:17:31.240 --> 00:17:32.380
Every little bit helps.

00:17:33.400 --> 00:17:33.960
Hey, Clark.

00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:35.460
Hey, Whitney. How's your dad?

00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:38.500
On the mend. Happy to be home.

00:17:40.279 --> 00:17:42.259
Hey, keep Saturday night free.

00:17:42.259 --> 00:17:45.299
I got two tickets to our town at the Metropolis Playhouse.

00:17:45.740 --> 00:17:48.019
Wow. What inspired you to do that?

00:17:48.240 --> 00:17:49.339
Saw you reading it at school.

00:17:50.259 --> 00:17:51.940
Probably might start making up for some lost time.

00:17:52.619 --> 00:17:53.480
You, uh...

00:17:53.480 --> 00:17:55.660
See ya.

00:17:56.619 --> 00:17:57.019
Bye.

00:18:03.619 --> 00:18:07.180
Whitney has paid more attention to me in the last two weeks than he has all year.

00:18:07.940 --> 00:18:09.000
Have you talked to him about it?

00:18:10.299 --> 00:18:12.240
Whitney seems so happy ever since his dad got back.

00:18:12.259 --> 00:18:14.660
He wants to pick up things where we left off.

00:18:15.400 --> 00:18:16.539
How do you feel about that?

00:18:18.140 --> 00:18:20.599
After Mr. Fordman got sick, Whitney needed me.

00:18:21.039 --> 00:18:22.279
Preparing to find our relationship.

00:18:23.359 --> 00:18:24.759
Now we need to redefine it.

00:18:25.759 --> 00:18:26.960
There's a lot of that going on.

00:18:28.779 --> 00:18:29.960
How are things with Chloe?

00:18:31.900 --> 00:18:32.299
Unresolved.

00:18:33.940 --> 00:18:34.779
What are you gonna do?

00:18:36.039 --> 00:18:36.740
I don't know.

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:39.259
I just don't want to lose a friend in the process.

00:18:40.140 --> 00:18:41.960
Once you cross that line, you can't go back.

00:18:42.259 --> 00:18:46.259
Chloe gave him that same advice about...

00:18:47.140 --> 00:18:47.920
someone else.

00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:50.839
What happened?

00:18:53.099 --> 00:18:54.480
We decided to stay friends.

00:18:56.079 --> 00:18:57.299
Do you regret that decision?

00:18:59.079 --> 00:18:59.480
Yeah.

00:19:00.339 --> 00:19:03.140
I let that moment slip away, and I don't think I'll ever get it back.

00:19:06.220 --> 00:19:07.940
I don't want to make that same mistake twice.

00:19:12.259 --> 00:19:12.940
Where are you going?

00:19:13.339 --> 00:19:14.819
I'm having a little awkward relationship with my mom.

00:19:14.819 --> 00:19:17.759
And you know you need to do anything to make up for it.

00:19:17.759 --> 00:19:19.259
We don't have plans tomorrow.

00:19:19.259 --> 00:19:20.059
But we need to talk.

00:19:20.460 --> 00:19:21.700
I'm intrigued.

00:19:21.700 --> 00:19:22.259
Right.

00:19:23.079 --> 00:19:24.259
I wish I could get you dead.

00:19:24.259 --> 00:19:25.299
Go get a job.

00:19:25.299 --> 00:19:26.140
Fred, don't regret it.

00:19:26.140 --> 00:19:27.759
GitHub about you was like a thunderbolt to him,

00:19:27.759 --> 00:19:28.859
giving you such a drink.

00:19:28.859 --> 00:19:30.420
We decide to get rid of that line if he'll say yes.

00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:32.019
It was basically what he always does.

00:19:32.019 --> 00:19:32.720
And of course Sedkowski wanted to stop recommend you

00:19:32.720 --> 00:19:33.099
fromizoing the잘

00:19:33.099 --> 00:19:33.940
but anyway.

00:19:35.140 --> 00:19:36.099
Hi, I'm Dad.

00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:38.140
How can I help you?

00:19:38.160 --> 00:19:40.099
Do you need Campanian high school?

00:19:40.099 --> 00:19:41.099
S tomato de sono, man.

00:19:41.099 --> 00:19:41.619
Yeah, of course.

00:19:41.619 --> 00:19:41.920
Thank you.

00:19:41.920 --> 00:19:42.160
You're welcome.

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:43.240
Oh, wow.

00:19:45.340 --> 00:19:46.360
It's beautiful.

00:19:47.660 --> 00:19:48.840
Well, so are you.

00:19:51.900 --> 00:19:54.740
Did you know after that car hit me and I was lying in the road,

00:19:56.120 --> 00:19:57.380
I kept picturing your face?

00:19:58.259 --> 00:19:58.779
Me?

00:19:59.820 --> 00:20:00.580
Why me?

00:20:01.820 --> 00:20:03.800
Because I always had the biggest crush on you.

00:20:04.279 --> 00:20:06.360
And I was too afraid to do anything about it.

00:20:06.800 --> 00:20:08.700
And I thought, here I am about to die.

00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:11.820
And I'm never going to get the chance to tell her how I feel.

00:20:12.160 --> 00:20:16.080
But when you started emailing me when I was in the hospital,

00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:19.800
I knew that this was my chance.

00:20:21.100 --> 00:20:22.880
I wasn't going to let you get away twice.

00:20:28.340 --> 00:20:29.820
I fought my way back for you.

00:20:29.820 --> 00:20:35.820
I fought my way back for you.

00:20:35.820 --> 00:20:39.500
Every time I have desire

00:20:39.500 --> 00:20:42.140
Every time I have desire

